The President recently met with national security officials to discuss our preparedness and security for the upcoming 13th anniversary of September 11th. This meeting was led by Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, Lisa Monaco. The goal was to review our security posture in light of global threats, including the threat posed by ISIL. The President's National Security team is actively working to prevent attacks on US soil and protect US citizens and facilities abroad, which are top national security priorities for the Administration.